Package com.github.actionfx.core.collections

Class ValueChangeAwareObservableList<E>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.github.actionfx.core.collections.ValueChangeAwareObservableList<E>
  • Type Parameters:
    E - the value type of the element
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Iterable<E>, java.util.Collection<E>, java.util.List<E>, javafx.beans.Observable, javafx.collections.ObservableList<E>
    public class ValueChangeAwareObservableList<E>
extends java.lang.Object
implements javafx.collections.ObservableList<E>
    Special implementation of ObservableList that is aware when values of list elements are changing. In that case, attached ListChangeListener are notified about that change.

    In order for this mechanism to work, we can of course not just "add" simple values, but we need to add observable instances of type ObservableValue.

    Please note that the actual list itself is immutable, i.e. that it is not possible to add to or remove elements from the list. In case an element is added or removed, an UnsupportedOperationException will be thrown.

    Author:
    koster
